<TITLE> Robbers loot jewellery shop in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  About 200 bhories of gold ornaments were looted in broad daylight Tuesday at gunpoint from a jewellery shop in capital's Taltola Super Market. Manager of Munni Jewellers Tazul Islam sustained knife injuries as he tackled one of the robbers. Rampura thana police sub-inspector Sazzad Hossain said that the owner of the shop claimed that up to 7-8 robbers stormed into the shop at around 2 pm. The police have launched a search for arresting the burglars. The present market price of the 200 bhories of gold ornaments will be at least Tk 6.0 millions, the manager claimed. bdnews2
